						<div class="postbody">And changing the BG and sprite pattern tables doesn't do anything surprising either?<br /><br />The way it looks like it works to me is:<br /><br />When sprites are 8x8, $5128-512B are not used at all. Sprites, BG, and data access via $2007 all use the banks selected via $5120-5127.<br /><br />When sprites are 8x16, sprites use $5120-5127, BG tiles use $5128-512B, and data access via $2007 uses the set that was written to most recently (writing to any of $5120-5127 last makes all data reads come from the sprite banks, writing to any of $5128-512B last makes all data reads come from the BG banks).<br /><br />Does that look right to you?<br /><br />Many thanks for your help.</div>

