						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">AWJ wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I strongly suspect that Bandit Kings of Ancient China <em>does</em> use split screen and extended attributes at the same time in its ending, and that whatever emulator was used to take the screenshots on GameFAQs doesn't emulate it correctly. That's the only explanation I can think of for <a href="https://www.gamefaqs.com/nes/587106-bandit-kings-of-ancient-china/images/223" class="postlink">this</a>.<br /></div>I'm about 80% certain that the credits scroll is using all the sprites for the pictures, and using the PPU's normal scroll registers for the letters.<br />(<a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=168503#p168503" class="postlink">Here's</a> what I said last time this came up).<br /><br />It really looks like no MMC5 boards were ever shipped with the SL3-6 jumpers shorted, so no MMC5 games could have used separate Y fine scrolls on a left-and-right split screen.</div>

